<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="483" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,1121,1326]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1193,1218]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was previously considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[973,1107,1193,1218]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pondolia">
<emphasis box="[973,1107,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">A. pondolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Onderstall" box="[1183,1367,1193,1218]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" refString="Onderstall, D. (1984) Descriptions of two new subspecies of Afroedura pondolia (Hewitt) and a discussion of species groups within the genus (Reptilia: Gekkonidae). Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 33, 497 - 509." type="journal article" year="1984">
Onderstall 
<number box="[1310,1367,1194,1218]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) until raised to specific status by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobsen" box="[459,637,1229,1254]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" refString="Jacobsen, N. H. G. (1990) A Herpetological Survey of the Transvaal. Unpublished Ph. D. Dissertation, University of Natal, Durban, South Africa, 1621 pp." type="book" year="1990">Jacobsen (1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobsen" box="[649,722,1230,1254]" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" refString="Jacobsen, N. H. G. (1992 a) Flat geckos (genus Afroedura) in the Transvaal. Journal of the Herpetological Association of Africa, 40, 22 - 25. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 04416651.1992.9650313" type="journal article" year="1992" yearSuffix="a">1992a</bibRefCitation>
). Six of the nine new species described herein are related to 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="langi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">A. langi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and earlier references to this species outside of its currently recognized range may refer to one or more of these taxa.
</paragraph>
